HEADWORD: Quab
<hw>Quab</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D. <ets>kwab</ets>
eelpout, Dan. <ets>quabbe</ets>, G. <ets>quabbe</ets>,
<ets>quappe</ets>, LG. <ets>quabbe</ets> a fat lump of flesh, and L.
<ets>capito</ets> a kind of fish with a large head, fr. <ets>caput</ets>
the head, also E. <ets>squab</ets>.]</ety> <def>An unfledged bird;
hence, something immature or unfinished.</def>
<rj><au>Ford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

